<font color="#FF0000">MUSINGS ON PAST MONTHS DIALOG</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jan  9  0:46:09 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
For so many, both vets and former protesters, there is a powerful urge to establish that one is right beyond a shadow of a doubt. We may not have been the &quot;good guys&quot; in everything done in Vietnam, but the North Vietnamese weren't the &quot;good guys&quot; either. It wasn't a nice clean splendid little war like Desert Storm. The South Vietnamese National Police made the worst of our current crop of corrupt politicians look like choir boys. Extortion and selling security clearances were daily affairs. Meanwhile the Communists were not above using children to gain an objective. The End was justified by any means available. That their victory was followed by a wholesale exodus was due to very real oppression. One fact commonly ignored is that persecution of ethnic Chinese was immediatly initiated. Here in Philadelphia, a rather large percentage of Vietnamese immigrants are from ethnic Chinese background.<br>
 I wrote a poem in Vietnam that I sent back to the student newspaper at Marquette University. A letter came back saying nothing about whether the poem was good, bad, or indifferent, but stated, &quot;How dare a baby killer like you assume to write poetry!&quot;. On arrival in California in July 69, I was told not to travel in uniform. I had it easy. The Vietnam War produced more Dear John letters per capita than any war in our history. More than one guy purposely stepped on a booby trap after one of these. Lately too many are dying too young. Out of 200 members of my VVA chapter we buried 8 in 7 months. If to some we seem to be &quot;whining&quot;, too many of us have been stepped on, lied to, and/or ignored too often, starting with our time in military service. As a group, Vietnam Vets are just not going to fade into the woodwork quietly. We quietly accepted the call to military service and after that - never again!
<p><code>-- turtle@plantaganet.com  (Gerald Alan Ney, The Herd, 68-69) </code><p>


